The Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) intends to award a firm-fixed-price commercial contract for subscription access to a web-based macroeconomic forecasting and analytical platform. The required subscription shall provide historical and forecast economic, financial, and demographic data at the national, state, and Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) levels; written economic analysis and commentary; data export capabilities; an Excel add-in; application programming interface (API) access; customer support; and annual user training. The contract will consist of a one-year base period and four one-year option periods. See the combined synopsis/solicitation and Performance Work Statement (PWS) for complete requirements.

